[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6885,
        "end_time": 12076,
        "text": "In 1984, an enterprising Australian doctor\nnamed Barry Marshall"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 12076,
        "end_time": 14186,
        "text": "decided to take a risk."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 14186,
        "end_time": 19016,
        "text": "Too many of his patients were complaining\nof severe abdominal pain"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 19016,
        "end_time": 20756,
        "text": "due to stomach ulcers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 20756,
        "end_time": 24957,
        "text": "which are sores in the lining\nof the upper intestinal tract."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 24957,
        "end_time": 28708,
        "text": "At the time, few effective treatments\nfor ulcers existed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 28708,
        "end_time": 33757,
        "text": "and many sufferers required\nhospitalization or even surgery."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 33757,
        "end_time": 35478,
        "text": "Desperate for answers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 35478,
        "end_time": 39506,
        "text": "Dr. Marshall swallowed a cloudy\nbroth of bacteria"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 39506,
        "end_time": 43418,
        "text": "collected from the stomach\nof one of his patients."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 43418,
        "end_time": 47287,
        "text": "Soon, Dr. Marshall was experiencing\nthe same abdominal pain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 47287,
        "end_time": 48098,
        "text": "bloating,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 48098,
        "end_time": 49540,
        "text": "and vomiting."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 49540,
        "end_time": 53468,
        "text": "Ten days later, a camera called \nan endoscope"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 53468,
        "end_time": 55979,
        "text": "peered inside his insides."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 55979,
        "end_time": 61278,
        "text": "Marshall&#39;s stomach was teeming\nwith the same bacteria as his patient."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 61278,
        "end_time": 66028,
        "text": "He&#39;d also developed gastritis,\nor severe inflammation of the stomach,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 66028,
        "end_time": 70388,
        "text": "the hallmark precursor of ulcers."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 70388,
        "end_time": 72230,
        "text": "Dr. Marshall&#39;s idea challenged"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 72230,
        "end_time": 76051,
        "text": "a misconception \nthat still persists to this day:"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 76051,
        "end_time": 78650,
        "text": "that ulcers are caused by stress,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 78650,
        "end_time": 79649,
        "text": "food,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 79649,
        "end_time": 82180,
        "text": "or too much stomach acid."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 82180,
        "end_time": 86007,
        "text": "Marshall thought the culprit\nwas bacterial infections."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 86007,
        "end_time": 88699,
        "text": "Initially, his idea was considered crazy"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 88699,
        "end_time": 91879,
        "text": "by the brightest medical \nminds on the planet."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 91879,
        "end_time": 97590,
        "text": "But in 2005, he and Dr. Robin Warren\nreceived the ultimate validation"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 97590,
        "end_time": 102610,
        "text": "when they were awarded the Nobel\nPrize for medicine."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 102610,
        "end_time": 107601,
        "text": "Our stomachs are J-shaped organs\nwith surprisingly intricate ecosystems"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 107601,
        "end_time": 110972,
        "text": "awash in hormones and chemicals."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 110972,
        "end_time": 114570,
        "text": "The stomach is under constant attack\nby digestive enzymes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 114570,
        "end_time": 115421,
        "text": "bile,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 115421,
        "end_time": 116412,
        "text": "proteins,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 116412,
        "end_time": 117381,
        "text": "microbes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 117381,
        "end_time": 120331,
        "text": "and the stomach&#39;s own acid."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 120331,
        "end_time": 122791,
        "text": "In response, it produces bicarbonate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 122791,
        "end_time": 123651,
        "text": "mucus,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 123651,
        "end_time": 127130,
        "text": "and phospholipids called prostaglandins"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 127130,
        "end_time": 130112,
        "text": "to maintain the integrity\nof its own lining."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 130112,
        "end_time": 132962,
        "text": "This delicate balance is constantly\nregulated"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 132962,
        "end_time": 136712,
        "text": "and referred to as mucosal defense."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 136712,
        "end_time": 143922,
        "text": "Since the mid-1800s, doctors thought\nstress alone caused most stomach ulcers."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 143922,
        "end_time": 146982,
        "text": "Patients were given antidepressants\nor tranquilizers"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 146982,
        "end_time": 150062,
        "text": "and told to visit health spas."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 150062,
        "end_time": 154923,
        "text": "This belief eventually shifted\nto the related notion of spicy foods"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 154923,
        "end_time": 157861,
        "text": "and stress as culprits."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 157861,
        "end_time": 162255,
        "text": "Yet no convincing study has ever\ndemonstrated that emotional upset,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 162255,
        "end_time": 163866,
        "text": "psychological distress,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 163866,
        "end_time": 165616,
        "text": "or spicy food"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 165616,
        "end_time": 170448,
        "text": "directly causes ulcer disease."
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 170448,
        "end_time": 175384,
        "text": "By the mid-20th century, it was widely\naccepted that excess hydrochloric acid"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 175384,
        "end_time": 178404,
        "text": "prompted the stomach to eat itself."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 178404,
        "end_time": 183821,
        "text": "Fervent proponents of this idea\nwere referred to as the acid mafia."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 183821,
        "end_time": 187683,
        "text": "The biggest hole in this theory\nwas that antiacids only provide"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 187683,
        "end_time": 190056,
        "text": "temporary relief."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 190056,
        "end_time": 192194,
        "text": "We now know that some rare ulcers"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 192194,
        "end_time": 196125,
        "text": "are indeed caused \nby too much hydrochloric acid."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 196125,
        "end_time": 200194,
        "text": "But they make up less than 1%\nof all cases."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 200194,
        "end_time": 204486,
        "text": "Dr. Marshall and Dr. Warren pinpointed\na spiral-shaped bacteria"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 204486,
        "end_time": 210619,
        "text": "called Helicobacter pylori,\nor H. pylori, as the real offender."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 210619,
        "end_time": 215189,
        "text": "H. pylori is one of humanity&#39;s oldest\nand most frequent companions,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 215189,
        "end_time": 218816,
        "text": "having joined us at least 50,000\nyears ago,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 218816,
        "end_time": 221985,
        "text": "and now found in 50% of people."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 221985,
        "end_time": 224365,
        "text": "Previously, we thought the stomach\nwas sterile"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 224365,
        "end_time": 228910,
        "text": "on account of it being such an acidic,\nhostile environment."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 228910,
        "end_time": 232286,
        "text": "Yet H. pylori survives the acidic turmoil\nof the stomach"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 232286,
        "end_time": 237486,
        "text": "with a variety of features that disrupt\nmucosal defense in its favor."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 237486,
        "end_time": 241176,
        "text": "For example, it produces an enzyme\ncalled urease"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 241176,
        "end_time": 245107,
        "text": "that helps protect it from \nthe surrounding gastric acid."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 245107,
        "end_time": 248437,
        "text": "H. pylori can make over 1,500 proteins,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 248437,
        "end_time": 253447,
        "text": "many of which are dedicated to maximizing\nits virulence."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 253447,
        "end_time": 255917,
        "text": "We still have unanswered questions,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 255917,
        "end_time": 260786,
        "text": "like why specific people develop ulcers\nat particular times."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 260786,
        "end_time": 263667,
        "text": "However, we do know individual genetics,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 263667,
        "end_time": 265197,
        "text": "other medical problems,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 265197,
        "end_time": 266957,
        "text": "use of certain medications,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 266957,
        "end_time": 267937,
        "text": "smoking,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 267937,
        "end_time": 274059,
        "text": "and the genetic diversity \nof Helicobacter strains all play a role."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 274059,
        "end_time": 279338,
        "text": "In particular, certain pain medications\nused to reduce inflammation in joints"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 279338,
        "end_time": 282098,
        "text": "have been discovered to work\nwith H. pylori"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 282098,
        "end_time": 285408,
        "text": "to create more severe stomach ulcers."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 285408,
        "end_time": 291698,
        "text": "Dr. Marshall ended up being fine after\nhis famous, albeit dangerous, experiment."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 291698,
        "end_time": 297429,
        "text": "He ingested a course of antibiotics\nsimilar to the ones taken now for ulcers."
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 297429,
        "end_time": 301139,
        "text": "To be treated by simple antibiotics\nis a modern triumph"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 301139,
        "end_time": 304989,
        "text": "for a disease that previously \nneeded surgery."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 304989,
        "end_time": 310541,
        "text": "Marshall&#39;s work also reminded us that\nscientific progress is not always smooth."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 310541,
        "end_time": 313361,
        "text": "But there&#39;s value in trusting \nyour proverbial,"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 313361,
        "end_time": 315960,
        "text": "and sometimes literal, gut."
    }
]